# Testing Rules (Low-Code Platform)

## Default Mindset
- Always start with exploratory testing before writing automation.
- Identify Critical Paths (CP) first; treat them as release gates.
- Prefer risk-based coverage over broad checkbox testing.

## Output Format (Mandatory)
- For exploratory: create a charter + session notes.
- For critical path: create a manual CP test case in /testcases/manual.
- For automation: implement in Playwright under /automation/playwright/tests.

## Critical Path Definition
A CP is any flow that impacts:
- Authentication / Authorization / Tenant isolation
- Payments / billing
- Data integrity (create/update/delete), auditability
- Messaging / documents / PII access
- Cross-app navigation / shared database writes

## Automation Criteria
Only automate if:
- UI selectors are stable OR we have data-testid
- Flow is deterministic enough (no flaky async without hooks)
- Test data strategy exists (seed/reset)
